The principal hosts of the adults are various wild and domestic ungulates. Carnivores are apparently secondary or occasional hosts. Larvae and nymphs are specific to various groups of small mammals (
Geevarghese & Dhanda 1987
; Kaiser & Hoogstraal 1963 , 1964 ;
Sharif 1928
;
Singh & Dhanda 1965
). Geographic distribution. South Asia and neighboring regions of Central Asia.
